		<title type="html"><![CDATA[How to change interface language on the fly]]></title>

		
		<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.sandboxie.com/phpBB3/viewtopic.php?t=6362&amp;p=41619#p41619"><![CDATA[
The proper way is to reinstall/upgrade Sandboxie on top of the existing installation while selecting a new language.  This would recreate Start menu shortcuts in the new language.<br><br>* * *<br><br>The not-so-proper way is to change the value <strong>Language</strong> of the following registry key:<br><br>HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\SbieSvc<br><br>Language numbers are listed here:<br><br><a href="http://www.sandboxie.com/index.php?CorporateInstallation" class="postlink">http://www.sandboxie.com/index.php?Corp ... stallation</a><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.sandboxie.com/phpBB3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3">tzuk</a> — Tue Sep 29, 2009 6:41 pm</p><hr />
